        {
          "field_name": "interest_calculation_method",
          "candidate_value": "Some chequing accounts will waive your monthly bank plan fee if you keep a minimum daily closing balance in your account.",
          "value_type": "string",
          "confidence": 0.97,
          "extraction_method": "heuristic_sentence",
          "source_document_id": "src-bmo-html-389a94cb4269c9e0",
          "source_snapshot_id": "snap-48888e159d335b8c",
          "evidence_chunk_id": "chunk-dd4cf89656023d29",
          "evidence_text_excerpt": "What counts as a transaction?\nBasically, any action you take that moves money out of your account counts as a transaction. Money coming into your account \u2013 like payroll direct deposits or cash deposits at an ATM A T M \u2013 don\u2019t count as transactions.\nWhat\u2019s a minimum monthly balance? Some chequing accounts will waive your monthly bank plan fee if you keep a minimum daily closing balance in your account. For example, Our BMO Performance Chequing Account has a monthly fee of $17.95 but if you keep at least $4,000 in your account, you won\u2019t be charged the monthly plan fee. Your account balance is calculated daily, so you need to maintain the minimum balance every day of the month to have your fee waived.",
          "anchor_type": "section",
          "anchor_value": "what-counts-as-a-transaction",
          "page_no": null,
          "chunk_index": 18,
          "field_metadata": {
