        {
          "field_name": "withdrawal_limit_text",
          "candidate_value": "Also, our BMO B M O Premium Chequing Account offers unlimited non- BMO ATM withdrawals and we won\u2019t charge you a fee.",
          "value_type": "string",
          "confidence": 0.7,
          "extraction_method": "heuristic_text",
          "source_document_id": "src-bmo-html-389a94cb4269c9e0",
          "source_snapshot_id": "snap-48888e159d335b8c",
          "evidence_chunk_id": "chunk-9c544177ada3320d",
          "evidence_text_excerpt": "Can I get unlimited Interac \u00ae\u2021 e-Transfer transactions?\nKeep in mind that if you have the Practical, Plus, Standard, i.connect or Enhanced Plan, each Interac e-Transfer transaction you send counts towards your Plan\u2019s monthly transaction limit.\nDoes BMO charge ATM fees? How can I avoid ATM fees abroad? When you use your BMO Debit Card to withdraw cash at a non- BMO ATM in or outside of Canada or a non- BMO Harris Bank ATM in the United States, we may charge a fee when you complete the transaction. If you find yourself using a non- BMO ATM frequently, you may consider asking a merchant for cash back when using your debit card to make a purchase. You get cash in hand and it saves you a trip to the bank! Also, our BMO B M O Premium Chequing Account offers unlimited non- BMO ATM withdrawals and we won\u2019t charge you a fee. Keep in mind that most ATM will charge a convenience fee that you will",
